----------++FUNCTION(TRKF120) FILES(6).

----------++VER(Z038).

----------++JCLIN RELFILE(1).

----------++MAC($$$$$DOC) DISTLIB(ASAMPLIB) SYSLIB(SAMPLIB) RELFILE(2).

----------++MAC($$$$CUST) DISTLIB(ASAMPLIB) SYSLIB(SAMPLIB) RELFILE(2).

                                      6 * NAME: ICHSEC00                                                     *  00060000
                                      7 *                                                                    *  00070000
                                      8 * TYPE: Assembler Source                                             *  00080000
                                      9 *                                                                    *  00090000
                                     10 * DESC: Initialize RAKF                                              *  00100000
                                     11 *                                                                    *  00110000
                                     12 * FUNCTION: - output banner to console                               *  00120000
                                     13 *           - check if SAFV is already defined and initialized       *  00130000
                                     14 *             o if yes: skip initialization and go directly to       *  00140000
                                     15 *                       profile and user table initialization        *  00150000
                                     16 *           - try to read initialization directive from              *  00160000
                                     17 *             parmlib member RAKFINIT:                               *  00170000
                                     18 *             o if first line of member starts with YES:    continue *  00180000
                                     19 *             o if first line of member starts with NO:     exit     *  00190000
                                     20 *             o else, of if member doesn't exist:                    *  00200000
                                     21 *               + ask operator for permission to initialize          *  00210000
                                     22 *                 if operator denies permission:            exit     *  00220000
                                     23 *           - get SQA storage for SAFV and initialize it             *  00230000
                                     24 *           - put entry address of SAF router ICHSFR00 in SAFV       *  00240000
                                     25 *           - initialize RCVT                                        *  00250000
                                     26 *           - initialize profile table                               *  00260000
                                     27 *           - initialize user table                                  *  00270000
                                     28 *                                                                    *  00280000
                                     29 * REQUIREMENTS: - ICHSFR00 in LPA                                    *  00290000
                                     30 *               - RAKFPROF and RAKFUSER in linklist                  *  00300000
                                     31 *               - parmlib defined through ddname IEFPARM             *  00310000
                                     32 *               - user and profile table DDs as needed               *  00320000
                                     33 *                 by RAKFPROF and RAKFUSER                           *  00330000
                                     34 *                                                                    *  00340000

----------++PTF(RRKF002) /*
---------- Make RACINIT Password Changes permanent */ .

----------++VER(Z038) FMID(TRKF120) PRE(RRKF001)
---------- /*
---------- Summary of Changes:
---------- -------------------
----------
---------- + Make RACINIT Password Changes permanent:
----------
----------   Before application of this PTF a new password supplied as NEWPASS
----------   parameter of a RACINIT macro was updated in the in-core users table
----------   only and thus lived until the in-core table was replaced by the
----------   contents of the source users table at RAKF intialization time or by
----------   running RAKFUSER. Thus users were able to change their passwords
----------   only temporary. Permanent password changes required an RAKF
----------   administrator to edit the RAKF users table manually.
----------
----------   This PTF changes processing of the NEWPASS parameter to queue the
----------   new password for update in the source users table in addition to
----------   updating the in-core users table. The password changes queue is
----------   applied during RAKFUSER processing to the source users table before
----------   the new in-core users table is created from the source table. This
----------   makes all password changes initiated by end users through using the
----------   password change facility of an application permanent and thus
----------   fully functional (for example changing the password at TSO logon
----------   time by entering currentpw/newpw at the "ENTER PASSWORD" prompt).
----------
---------- + introduce change history to source member ICHSFR00
----------
---------- Special Installation Instructions:
---------- ----------------------------------
----------
---------- 1. This PTF modifies elements that are not provided inline. These
----------    elements will be read during APPLY and ACCEPT processing from
----------    a PDS pointed to by ddname ELEMENTS. File RRKF002.elements.zip
----------    contains this PDS in XMIT370 format. Before the PTF can be APPLIed
----------    or ACCEPTed the PDS needs to be RECEIVed with an arbitrary name and
----------    a //ELEMENTS DD DSN=.... statement pointing to the PDS needs to
----------    be added to the SMP jobs used for APPLYing or ACCEPTing PTFs. After     DATE 21.216  TIME 08:12:18      HMASMP LVL 04.44 MESSAGES AND CONTROL STATEMENTS                        PAGE 0002

----------    the PTF has been APPLIed (and ACCEPTed if desired) the PDS can be
----------    deleted and the //ELEMENTS DD statement can be removed from the
----------    SMP jobs.
----------
----------    The following steps can be used to RECEIVE the PDS from file
----------    RRKF002.elements.zip:
----------
----------    o Unzip rrkf002.elements.xmi from RRKF002.elements.zip and upload
----------      it to dataset RAKF.RRKF002.ELEMENTS.XMI (LRECL=80,RECFM=FB) on
----------      your MVS system using your standard unzip utility and upload
----------      software.
----------
----------    o Submit the following job (requires the RECV370 utility to be
----------      installed, of course):
----------
----------      //RCVELEMS JOB ...
----------      //RECV370  EXEC PGM=RECV370
----------      //RECVLOG   DD SYSOUT=*
----------      //XMITIN    DD DSN=RAKF.RRKF002.ELEMENTS.XMI,DISP=SHR
----------      //SYSPRINT  DD SYSOUT=*
----------      //SYSUT1    DD DSN=&&SYSUT1,
----------      //             UNIT=SYSDA,
----------      //             SPACE=(CYL,(10,5)),
----------      //             DISP=(,DELETE,DELETE)
----------      //SYSUT2    DD DSN=RAKF.RRKF002.ELEMENTS,
----------      //             DISP=(,CATLG),SPACE=(TRK,(6,2,1),RLSE),
----------      //             DCB=(LRECL=80,BLKSIZE=5600,RECFM=FB),
----------      //             UNIT=SYSDA
----------      //SYSIN     DD DUMMY
----------      //SYSUDUMP  DD SYSOUT=*
----------
----------    The dataset names used in this example can be changed to anything
----------    you like as long as the //ELEMENT DD statement in the SMP APPLY
----------    and ACCEPT jobs points to the dataset created by //SYSUT2 DD of
----------    the RCVELEMS job.
----------
---------- 2. RECEIVE and APPLY the PTF as usual. Don't IPL the system!
----------
---------- 3. Perform step 1. b) from member $$$$CUST in HLQ.SAMPLIB (HLQ = high
----------    level qualifier of the RAKF libraries) to define the RAKF
----------    password changes queue dataset.
----------
---------- 4. Perform step 4 from member $$$$CUST in HLQ.SAMPLIB to add the RAKF
----------    password changes queue dataset DD statement to MSTRJCL. The sample
----------    usermod ZJW0003 provided in HLQ.SAMPLIB has been adapted by this
----------    PTF and can be rerun without changes if the original version had
----------    been used at RAKF installation time.
----------
---------- 5. IPL the system using the CLPA option.
----------
---------- 6. ACCEPT the PTF according to your preferences after sufficient
----------    testing.
---------- */ .

----------++JCLIN .

----------++SRCUPD(ICHSFR00) .

----------++SRCUPD(RAKFPWUP) .     DATE 21.216  TIME 08:12:18      HMASMP LVL 04.44 MESSAGES AND CONTROL STATEMENTS                        PAGE 0003

----------++PTF(RRKF003) /*
---------- Security Enhancement in Users and Profiles Tables Processing */ .

----------++VER(Z038) FMID(TRKF120) PRE(RRKF001,RRKF002)
---------- /*
---------- Summary of Changes:
---------- -------------------
----------
---------- + Security Enhancement in Users and Profiles Tables Processing:
----------
----------   The in-core users and profiles tables which control RAKF's access
----------   decisions are maintained by editing source versions of these tables
----------   and using the utilities RAKFUSER and RAKFPROF to replace the in-core
----------   tables with the current source tables to activate changes.
----------
----------   Although typically access to the source tables will be restricted
----------   to users and/or groups responsible for security administration a
----------   malicious user could take over control of the security environment
----------   by creating private versions of the source tables and running
----------   RAKFUSER and RAKFPROF to replace the in-core tables from the private
----------   source. MVS 3.8j doesn't call the security product for access
----------   verification through the PROGRAM class before executing a program which
----------   would in later versions of MVS be the way to protect the utilities from
----------   unauthorized use.
----------
----------   PTF RRKF003 introduces a request for READ access to profile RAKFADM
----------   in the FACILITY class before updating the in-core tables. To prevent
----------   unwanted accesses to the RAKFUSER or RAKFPROF utilities define profile
----------   RAKFADM in the FACILITY class with universal access NONE and grant
----------   only RAKF administration users or groups READ access to this profile.
----------
---------- Special Installation Instructions:
---------- ----------------------------------
----------
---------- None
----------
---------- */ .

----------++SRCUPD(RAKFPROF) .
     DATE 21.216  TIME 08:12:23      HMASMP LVL 04.44 MESSAGES AND CONTROL STATEMENTS                        PAGE 0002

----------++SRCUPD(RAKFUSER) .

     SYSMOD   STATUS     TYPE      ------------------------

----------++PTF(RRKF004) /*
---------- RAKF User's Guide */ .

----------++VER(Z038) FMID(TRKF120) PRE(RRKF001,RRKF002,RRKF003)
---------- /*
---------- Summary of Changes:
---------- -------------------
----------
---------- + RAKF User's Guide:
----------
----------   RAKF documention was widespread over 5 SAMPLIB members referencing
----------   each other: $$$$INST, $$$$CUST, $$$$M38J, $$$$RMVE and $$$$$DOC.
----------   This documentation had been written at different stages of the
----------   evolution from the ESG Security System to RAKF and became increasingly
----------   difficult to read as newer parts often invalidated parts of the
----------   older documentation. In addition the total amount of documentation
----------   materials exceeds the size that can be edited with reasonable effort
----------   in handcrafted text files with fixed length 80 byte records.
----------
----------   With this PTF the documentation is republished as the "RAKF Version 1
----------   Release 2 Modifaction 0 User's Guide" which is available in two
----------   formats:
----------
----------   o Microsoft Word 2010 .docx:        The source document ("original
----------                                       copy") and base for further
----------                                       evolutions.
----------
----------   o Portable Document Format (PDF/A): Display and printer friendly
----------                                       format intended for reading or
----------                                       printing the document using
----------                                       publicly available no-cost
----------                                       software (Adobe Acrobat Reader).
----------
----------   These two formats are made available as member $DOC$ZIP in SAMPLIB
----------   which is a zip archive containing the two files "Users_Guide.docx"
----------   and "Users_Guide.pdf". This member is intended to be downloaded in
----------   binary format to the user's PC using the 3270 terminal emulation's
----------   file transfer function (typically based on IND$FILE) or any other
----------   suitable method.
----------     DATE 21.216  TIME 08:12:28      HMASMP LVL 04.44 MESSAGES AND CONTROL STATEMENTS                        PAGE 0002

----------   Once downloaded, the User's Guide can be extracted in the desired
----------   format (.pdf or .docx) using the PC's standard unzip utility for
----------   reading or printing using Word, Acrobat Reader or other tools
----------   compatible with these formats.
----------
----------   With the installation of this PTF the original documentation members
----------   $$$$INST, $$$$CUST, $$$$M38J and $$$$RMVE become obsolete and are
----------   deleted from SAMPLIB. Member $$$$$DOC, which is the original
----------   documentation of the ESG Security System prepared by Sam Golob in
----------   1991, is retained in SAMPLIB as a historical reference.
----------
---------- Special Installation Instructions:
---------- ----------------------------------
----------
---------- 1. This PTF modifies elements that are not provided inline. These
----------    elements will be read during APPLY and ACCEPT processing from
----------    a PDS pointed to by ddname DOCLIB. File RRKF004.doclib.zip
----------    contains this PDS in XMIT370 format. Before the PTF can be APPLIed
----------    or ACCEPTed the PDS needs to be RECEIVed with an arbitrary name and
----------    a //DOCLIB DD DSN=.... statement pointing to the PDS needs to
----------    be added to the SMP jobs used for APPLYing or ACCEPTing PTFs. After
----------    the PTF has been APPLIed (and ACCEPTed if desired) the PDS can be
----------    deleted and the //DOCLIB DD statement can be removed from the
----------    SMP jobs.
----------
----------    The following steps can be used to RECEIVE the PDS from file
----------    RRKF004.doclib.zip:
----------
----------    o Unzip RRKF004.doclib.xmi from RRKF004.doclib.zip and upload
----------      it to dataset RAKF.RRKF004.DOCLIB.XMI (LRECL=80,RECFM=FB) on
----------      your MVS system using your standard unzip utility and upload
----------      software (use binary mode for upload!)
----------
----------    o Submit the following job (requires the RECV370 utility to be
----------      installed, of course):
----------
----------      //RCVDOCS  JOB ...
----------      //RECV370  EXEC PGM=RECV370
----------      //RECVLOG   DD SYSOUT=*
----------      //XMITIN    DD DSN=RAKF.RRKF004.DOCLIB.XMI,DISP=SHR
----------      //SYSPRINT  DD SYSOUT=*
----------      //SYSUT1    DD DSN=&&SYSUT1,
----------      //             UNIT=SYSDA,
----------      //             SPACE=(CYL,(10,5)),
----------      //             DISP=(,DELETE,DELETE)
----------      //SYSUT2    DD DSN=RAKF.RRKF004.DOCLIB,
----------      //             DISP=(,CATLG),SPACE=(TRK,(30,15,1),RLSE),
----------      //             DCB=(LRECL=80,BLKSIZE=5600,RECFM=FB),
----------      //             UNIT=SYSDA
----------      //SYSIN     DD DUMMY
----------      //SYSUDUMP  DD SYSOUT=*
----------
----------    The dataset names used in this example can be changed to anything
----------    you like as long as the //DOCLIB DD statement in the SMP APPLY
----------    and ACCEPT jobs points to the dataset created by //SYSUT2 DD of
----------    the RCVDOCS job.
----------
---------- 2. RECEIVE, APPLY and ACCEPT the PTF as usual.
----------     DATE 21.216  TIME 08:12:28      HMASMP LVL 04.44 MESSAGES AND CONTROL STATEMENTS                        PAGE 0003

---------- */ .

----------++MAC($$$$INFO) SSI(02040000) .

----------++MAC($DOC$ZIP) TXLIB(DOCLIB) DISTLIB(ASAMPLIB) SYSLIB(SAMPLIB) .

----------++MAC($$$$CUST) DELETE .

----------++MAC($$$$INST) DELETE .

----------++MAC($$$$M38J) DELETE .

----------++MAC($$$$RMVE) DELETE .

----------++PTF(RRKF005) /*
---------- RACIND Utility to control VSAM RACF Indicators */ .

----------++VER(Z038) FMID(TRKF120) PRE(RRKF001,RRKF002,RRKF003,RRKF004)
---------- /*
---------- Summary of Changes:
---------- -------------------
----------
---------- + RACIND Utility to control VSAM RACF Indicators
----------
----------   This PTF adds a new utility named RACIND to RAKF. RACIND allows
----------   to switch the RACF indicator of any VSAM catalog entry on or off,
----------   thus enabling easy indication and unindication of the system's VSAM
----------   catalogs and objects.
----------
----------   SAMPLIB member RACIND is a sample job stream illustrating the use
----------   of the RACIND utility.
----------
---------- Special Installation Instructions:
---------- ----------------------------------
----------
---------- 1. This PTF adds elements that are not provided inline. These
----------    elements will be read during APPLY and ACCEPT processing from
----------    a PDS pointed to by ddname RACIND. File RRKF005.racind.zip
----------    contains this PDS in XMIT370 format. Before the PTF can be APPLIed
----------    or ACCEPTed the PDS needs to be RECEIVed with an arbitrary name and
----------    a //RACIND DD DSN=.... statement pointing to the PDS needs to
----------    be added to the SMP jobs used for APPLYing or ACCEPTing PTFs. After
----------    the PTF has been APPLIed (and ACCEPTed if desired) the PDS can be
----------    deleted and the //RACIND DD statement can be removed from the
----------    SMP jobs.
----------
----------    The following steps can be used to RECEIVE the PDS from file
----------    RRKF005.racind.zip:
----------
----------    o Unzip RRKF005.RACIND.XMI from RRKF005.racind.zip and upload
----------      it to dataset RAKF.RRKF005.RACIND.XMI (LRECL=80,RECFM=FB) on
----------      your MVS system using your standard unzip utility and upload
----------      software.
----------     DATE 21.216  TIME 08:12:32      HMASMP LVL 04.44 MESSAGES AND CONTROL STATEMENTS                        PAGE 0002

----------    o Submit the following job (requires the RECV370 utility to be
----------      installed, of course):
----------
----------      //RCVIND   JOB ...
----------      //RECV370  EXEC PGM=RECV370
----------      //RECVLOG   DD SYSOUT=*
----------      //XMITIN    DD DSN=RAKF.RRKF005.RACIND.XMI,DISP=SHR
----------      //SYSPRINT  DD SYSOUT=*
----------      //SYSUT1    DD DSN=&&SYSUT1,
----------      //             UNIT=SYSDA,
----------      //             SPACE=(CYL,(10,5)),
----------      //             DISP=(,DELETE,DELETE)
----------      //SYSUT2    DD DSN=RAKF.RRKF005.RACIND,
----------      //             DISP=(,CATLG),SPACE=(TRK,(6,3,1),RLSE),
----------      //             DCB=(LRECL=80,BLKSIZE=5600,RECFM=FB),
----------      //             UNIT=SYSDA
----------      //SYSIN     DD DUMMY
----------      //SYSUDUMP  DD SYSOUT=*
----------
----------    The dataset names used in this example can be changed to anything
----------    you like as long as the //RACIND DD statement in the SMP APPLY
----------    and ACCEPT jobs points to the dataset created by //SYSUT2 DD of
----------    the RCVIND job.
----------
---------- 2. RECEIVE and APPLY the PTF as usual.
----------
---------- 3. ACCEPT the PTF according to your preferences after sufficient
----------    testing.
---------- */ .

----------++JCLIN .

----------++PTF(RRKF006) /*
---------- Sample jobs to RACF indicate or unindicate the whole system */ .

----------++VER(Z038) FMID(TRKF120) PRE(RRKF001,RRKF002,RRKF003,RRKF004,RRKF005)
---------- /*
---------- Summary of Changes:
---------- -------------------
----------
---------- + Sample jobs to RACF indicate or unindicate the whole system
----------
----------   These jobs provide a fully automated way to set or clear the RACF
----------   indicators of all eligible datasets, VSAM objects and catalogs in
----------   the system.
----------
---------- + OCO distribution of RAKF-external utilities
----------
----------   The sample jobs for RACF indication or unindication need some
----------   utilities from other sources than RAKF. To ease installation of
----------   these utilities they are collected to an XMI file containing the
----------   modules needed and a sample job to install them from this XMI file
----------   is provided. The User's Guide describes the procedure to install
----------   these utilities as well as the original source from which they
----------   were derived.
----------
---------- + Sample jobs for creation of SYS1.SECURE.CNTL and SYS1.SECURE.PWUP
----------
----------   These jobs are provided to help with the initial customization
----------   tasks on systems not having interactive dataset allocation and
----------   or move/copy utilities available.
----------
---------- + add missing //RAKFPWUP DD statement to the RAKF cataloged procedure
----------
---------- + update the RAKF User's Guide with changes introduced since RRKF004
----------
---------- Special Installation Instructions:
---------- ----------------------------------
----------
---------- 1. Due to the large amount of new sample and documentation material
----------    the space allocation of hlq.SAMPLIB and hlq.ASAMPLIB needs to be
----------    enlarged to avoid space related abends during installation of this     DATE 21.216  TIME 08:12:37      HMASMP LVL 04.44 MESSAGES AND CONTROL STATEMENTS                        PAGE 0002

----------    PTF. Please reallocate these libraries to meet the following
----------    definitions (calculation based on 3350 type DASD):
----------
----------    //ASAMPLIB DD  DISP=(,CATLG),DSN=hlq.ASAMPLIB,VOL=SER=dddddd,
----------    //             UNIT=SYSDA,DCB=(RECFM=FB,LRECL=80,BLKSIZE=19040),
----------    //             SPACE=(TRK,(120,40,10))
----------    //SAMPLIB  DD  DISP=(,CATLG),DSN=hlq.SAMPLIB,VOL=SER=ssssss,
----------    //             UNIT=SYSDA,DCB=(RECFM=FB,LRECL=80,BLKSIZE=19040),
----------    //             SPACE=(TRK,(120,40,10))
----------
----------    Of course, the original contents needs to be copied into the
----------    newly allocated libraries!
----------
---------- 2. This PTF adds elements that are not provided inline. These
----------    elements will be read during APPLY and ACCEPT processing from
----------    a PDS pointed to by ddname RRKF006E. File RRKF006E.zip
----------    contains this PDS in XMIT370 format. Before the PTF can be APPLIed
----------    or ACCEPTed the PDS needs to be RECEIVed with an arbitrary name and
----------    an //RRKF006E DD DSN=.... statement pointing to the PDS needs to
----------    be added to the SMP jobs used for APPLYing or ACCEPTing PTFs. After
----------    the PTF has been APPLIed (and ACCEPTed if desired) the PDS can be
----------    deleted and the //RRKF006E DD statement can be removed from the
----------    SMP jobs.
----------
----------    The following steps can be used to RECEIVE the PDS from file
----------    RRKF006E.zip:
----------
----------    o Unzip RRKF006E.XMI from RRKF006E.zip and upload
----------      it to dataset RAKF.RRKF006E.XMI (LRECL=80,RECFM=FB) on
----------      your MVS system using your standard unzip utility and upload
----------      software.
----------
----------    o Submit the following job (requires the RECV370 utility to be
----------      installed, of course):
----------
----------      //RCVTLIB  JOB ...
----------      //RECV370  EXEC PGM=RECV370
----------      //RECVLOG   DD SYSOUT=*
----------      //XMITIN    DD DSN=RAKF.RRKF006E.XMI,DISP=SHR
----------      //SYSPRINT  DD SYSOUT=*
----------      //SYSUT1    DD DSN=&&SYSUT1,
----------      //             UNIT=SYSDA,
----------      //             SPACE=(CYL,(10,5)),
----------      //             DISP=(,DELETE,DELETE)
----------      //SYSUT2    DD DSN=RAKF.RRKF006E,
----------      //             DISP=(,CATLG),SPACE=(TRK,(6,3,1),RLSE),
----------      //             DCB=(LRECL=80,BLKSIZE=5600,RECFM=FB),
----------      //             UNIT=SYSDA
----------      //SYSIN     DD DUMMY
----------      //SYSUDUMP  DD SYSOUT=*
----------
----------    The dataset names used in this example can be changed to anything
----------    you like as long as the //RRKF006E DD statement in the SMP APPLY
----------    and ACCEPT jobs points to the dataset created by //SYSUT2 DD of
----------    the RCVTLIB job.
----------
---------- 3. RECEIVE and APPLY the PTF as usual.
----------
---------- 4. ACCEPT the PTF according to your preferences after sufficient     DATE 21.216  TIME 08:12:37      HMASMP LVL 04.44 MESSAGES AND CONTROL STATEMENTS                        PAGE 0003

----------    testing.
---------- */ .

000000                                2 RAKFPSAV CSECT                                                          00020000
                                      3          PRINT NOGEN                                                    00030000
                                      4 *                                                                       00040000
                                      5 **********************************************************************  00050000
                                      6 *                                                                    *  00060000
                                      7 * NAME: RAKFPSAV                                                     *  00070000
                                      8 *                                                                    *  00080000
                                      9 * TYPE: Assembler Source                                             *  00090000
                                     10 *                                                                    *  00100000
                                     11 * DESC: Save Password Changes in RAKF Users Table                    *  00110000
                                     12 *                                                                    *  00120000
                                     13 * FUNCTION: - read the password change queue created by RAKFPWUP     *  00130000
                                     14 *             into memory                                            *  00140000
                                     15 *           - loop through the RAKF users table and check each line  *  00150000
                                     16 *             for a password change queue entry. If an entry exists  *  00160000
                                     17 *             update that line in place                              *  00170000
                                     18 *           - clear the password change queue                        *  00180000
                                     19 *                                                                    *  00190000
                                     20 * REQUIREMENTS: - RAKF users table pointed to by ddname RAKFUSER     *  00200000
                                     21 *               - RAKF password change queue pointed to by ddname    *  00210000
                                     22 *                 RAKFPWUP, a sequential dataset with LRECL=18,      *  00220000
                                     23 *                 RECFM=F and one line per password change in the    *  00230000
                                     24 *                 following format:                                  *  00240000
                                     25 *                                                                    *  00250000
                                     26 *                 ----+----1----+---                                 *  00260000
                                     27 *                 uuuuuuuu pppppppp                                  *  00270000
                                     28 *                                                                    *  00280000
                                     29 *                 where uuuuuuuu is the username and pppppppp is     *  00290000
                                     30 *                 the new password, each padded to the right with    *  00300000
                                     31 *                 blanks to 8 characters.                            *  00310000
                                     32 *                                                                    *  00320000
                                     33 **********************************************************************  00330000
                                     34 *                                                                       00340000
                                     35 * initialize                                                            00350000
                                     36 *                                                                       00360000
                                     37          SAVE  (14,12),,RAKFPSAV_&SYSDATE._&SYSTIME                     00370000

00002C 18DB                          48          LR    R13,R11             setup => our savearea                00420000
                            00034    49          USING SAVEAREA,R13        new addressability                   00430000

                                     55 *                                                                       00490000

               * FUNCTION: - retrieve username and new password from CSA area       *  00130000     *       REPLACEMENT*
               *           - append username and new password to update queue       *  00140000     *          REPLACED*
               *             allocated by ICHSFR00 in subpool 227 (fetch protected) *  00140000     *       REPLACEMENT*
               *                                                                    *  00150000     *          REPLACED*
               *           - clear and free CSA area                                *  00150000     *       REPLACEMENT*
               * NOTE: Yet to be implemented!                                       *  00160000     *          REPLACED*
               *           - append username and new password to the RAKF password  *  00160000     *       REPLACEMENT*
               *                                                                    *  00170000     *          REPLACED*
               *             change queue, a sequential dataset with LRECL=18,      *  00170000     *       REPLACEMENT*
               **********************************************************************  00180000     *          REPLACED*
               *             RECFM=F containing one line per password change in the *  00180000     *       REPLACEMENT*
               *                                                                       00190000     *          REPLACED*
               *             following format:                                      *  00190000     *       REPLACEMENT*
                        PRINT NOGEN                                                    00200000     *          REPLACED*
               *                                                                    *  00200000     *       REPLACEMENT*
                        XR    15,15                                                    00210000     *          REPLACED*
               *             ----+----1----+---                                     *  00210000     *       REPLACEMENT*
                        BR    14                                                       00220000     *          REPLACED*
               *             uuuuuuuu pppppppp                                      *  00220000     *       REPLACEMENT*
                        END   RAKFPWUP                                                 00230000     *          REPLACED*
               *                                                                    *  00230000     *       REPLACEMENT*
               *             where uuuuuuuu is the username and pppppppp is the new *  00240000     *          INSERTED*
               *             password, each padded to the right with blanks to 8    *  00250000     *          INSERTED*
               *             characters.                                            *  00260000     *          INSERTED*
               *                                                                    *  00270000     *          INSERTED*
               * REQUIREMENTS: - RAKF password change queue pointed to by ddname    *  00280000     *          INSERTED*
               *                 RAKFPWUP using DISP=MOD in the DD statement.       *  00290000     *          INSERTED*
               *                                                                    *  00300000     *          INSERTED*
               **********************************************************************  00310000     *          INSERTED*
               *                                                                       00320000     *          INSERTED*       SYSIN                            NEW MASTER                                        IEBUPDTE LOG PAGE 0002


               * initialize                                                            00330000     *          INSERTED*
               *                                                                       00340000     *          INSERTED*
                        SAVE  (14,12),,RAKFPWUP_&SYSDATE._&SYSTIME                     00350000     *          INSERTED*
                        USING RAKFPWUP,R15        establish => program EP              00360000     *          INSERTED*
                        ST    R13,SAVEAREA+4      save HSA                             00370000     *          INSERTED*
                        LA    R11,SAVEAREA        establish => savearea                00380000     *          INSERTED*
                        ST    R11,8(R13)          save LSA                             00390000     *          INSERTED*
                        LR    R13,R11             setup => our savearea                00400000     *          INSERTED*
                        USING SAVEAREA,R13        new addressability                   00410000     *          INSERTED*
                        DROP  R15                 program EP no longer needed          00420000     *          INSERTED*
                        B     CONTINUE            branch around savearea               00430000     *          INSERTED*
               SAVEAREA DS    18F                 savearea                             00440000     *          INSERTED*
               *                                                                       00450000     *          INSERTED*
               * Begin of code                                                         00460000     *          INSERTED*
               *                                                                       00470000     *          INSERTED*
               CONTINUE LR    R5,R1               remember PARM plist address          00480000     *          INSERTED*
                        MODESET MODE=SUP,KEY=ZERO authorize ourselves                  00490000     *          INSERTED*
                        L     R1,0(,R5)           address of PARM field plist          00500000     *          INSERTED*
                        LH    R5,0(,R1)           length of PARM field                 00510000     *          INSERTED*
                        CH    R5,=H'8'            is PARM field length 8 characters?   00520000     *          INSERTED*
                        BNE   INVPARM              talk dirrty and exit if not         00530000     *          INSERTED*
                        MVC   ADDRHEX,2(R1)       get PARM field in check plist        00540000     *          INSERTED*
                        MVC   ADDRUNPK,2(R1)      get PARM field for translate         00550000     *          INSERTED*
                        TR    ADDRUNPK,HEXTBL     translate PARM field to zoned        00560000     *          INSERTED*
                        PACK  ADDRESS(5),ADDRUNPK(9) pack PARM field                   00570000     *          INSERTED*
                        L     R1,ADDRESS          address storage pointed to by PARM   00580000     *          INSERTED*
                        CLC   0(LPWUPCMD,R1),STRTPWUP parmlist from ICHSFR00 found?    00590000     *          INSERTED*
                        BNE   INVPARM              talk dirrty and exit if not         00600000     *          INSERTED*
                        MVC   PWUPUSER(8),PWUPUSER-STRTPWUP(R1) get user               00610000     *          INSERTED*
                        MVC   PWUPPSWD(8),PWUPPSWD-STRTPWUP(R1) get new password       00620000     *          INSERTED*
                        XC    0(LPWUP,R1),0(R1)   clear ICHSFR00 parmlist storage      00630000     *          INSERTED*
                        FREEMAIN RU,LV=LPWUP,A=ADDRESS,SP=227 free parmlist storage    00640000     *          INSERTED*
                        ENQ    (SECURITY,USERS,E,,SYSTEM),RET=HAVE serialization       00650000     *          INSERTED*
                        OPEN  (QUEUE,(OUTPUT))    open password change queue           00660000     *          INSERTED*
                        PUT   QUEUE,PWUP          write entry                          00670000     *          INSERTED*
                        CLOSE (QUEUE)             close password change queue          00680000     *          INSERTED*
                        DEQ   (SECURITY,USERS,,SYSTEM) release ENQ                     00690000     *          INSERTED*
                        MVC   SUCCESS+38(8),PWUPUSER move user into success message    00700000     *          INSERTED*
                        WTO   MF=(E,SUCCESS)      tell operator                        00710000     *          INSERTED*
               *                                                                       00720000     *          INSERTED*
               * return                                                                00730000     *          INSERTED*
               *                                                                       00740000     *          INSERTED*
               RETURN   MODESET MODE=PROB,KEY=NZERO return to problem state            00750000     *          INSERTED*
                        L     R13,SAVEAREA+4      get caller's savearea                00760000     *          INSERTED*
                        RETURN (14,12),,RC=0      return                               00770000     *          INSERTED*
               INVPARM  WTO   'RAKF006W invalid password update request ignored'       00780000     *          INSERTED*
                        B     RETURN                                                   00790000     *          INSERTED*
               *                                                                       00800000     *          INSERTED*
               * data area                                                             00810000     *          INSERTED*
               *                                                                       00820000     *          INSERTED*
               STRTPWUP DC    AL2(LPWUPCMD)       parameter list that must have been.. 00830000     *          INSERTED*
                        DC    X'0000'               .. used to start this RAKFPWUP ..  00840000     *          INSERTED*       SYSIN                            NEW MASTER                                        IEBUPDTE LOG PAGE 0003


                        DC    C'S RAKFPWUP,PARM=''' .. run. This is used to perform .. 00850000     *          INSERTED*

  146     //SMPCNTL  DD  *
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          *** Allocate the RAKF password queue dataset SYS1.SECURE.PWUP         *
          ***                                                                   *
          *** Expected return codes: Step DELETE:  00                           *
          ***                        Step SCRATCH: 08 or lower                  *
          ***                        Step ALLOC:   00                           *
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          ***
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          *** Delete SYS1.SECURE.PWUP,SYS1.SECURE.CNTL                          *
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
  147     //LISTCAT  EXEC PGM=IDCAMS
  148     //SYSPRINT DD SYSOUT=*
  149     //SYSIN    DD *
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          *** Scratch SYS1.SECURE.PWUP                                          *
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
  150     //SCRATCH EXEC PGM=IEHPROGM
  151     //SYSPRINT DD  SYSOUT=*
  152     //DD1      DD  VOL=SER=MVS000,DISP=OLD,UNIT=3350
  153     //SYSIN    DD  *
  154     //IBMUSER EXEC TSODUSER,ID=IBMUSER
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          *** Allocate SYS1.SECURE.PWUP                                         *
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          ***                                                                     00000010
          *** PROCEDURE TO DELETE TSO USER ID TO SYS1.UADS AND (OPTIONALLY)       00000020
          *** DELETE ALL FILES ASSOCIATED WITH THE USER ID                        00000030
          ***                                                                     00000040
  155     XXTSODUSER PROC ID=,              TSO USER ID                          +00000050
          XX             KEEP='YES'         RETAIN USER'S FILES?                  00000060
          ***                                                                     00000070
          *** EVALUATE KEEPFILES PARAMETER                                        00000080
          ***                                                                     00000090
  156     XXEVAL01   EXEC PGM=PSU001,PARM=('&KEEP,EQ,YES')                        00000100
  157     XXSTEPLIB  DD  DSN=SYSC.LINKLIB,DISP=SHR                                00000110
          ***                                                                     00000120
          *** GENERATE COMMAND FILE TO DELETE TSO USER'S PROFILE                  00000130
          ***                                                                     00000140
  158     XXPW02     EXEC PGM=PSU002,PARM=('\',                                   00000150
          XX             ' PROFILE NOPREFIX\',                                    00000160
          XX             ' ACCOUNT\',                                             00000170
          XX             '   SYNC\',                                              00000180
          XX             '   DELETE (&ID.)\',                                     00000190
          XX             '   SYNC\',                                              00000200
          XX             '   END')                                                00000210
  159     XXSTEPLIB  DD  DSN=SYSC.LINKLIB,DISP=SHR                                00000220
  160     XXSYSOUT   DD  DSN=&&ACCOUNT,DISP=(,PASS),                              00000230
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,SPACE=(TRK,(15)),                             00000240
          XX             DCB=(RECFM=FB,LRECL=80,BLKSIZE=3120)                     00000250
          ***                                                                     00000260
          *** DELETE TSO USER'S PROFILE                                           00000270
          ***                                                                     00000280
  161     XXTSO03    EXEC PGM=IKJEFT01,REGION=4096K                               00000290
  162     XXSYSUADS   DD DSN=SYS1.UADS,DISP=SHR                                   00000300
  163     XXSYSLBC    DD DSN=SYS1.BRODCAST,DISP=SHR                               00000310
  164     XXSYSTSPRT  DD SYSOUT=*                                                 00000320
  165     XXSYSTSIN   DD DSN=&&ACCOUNT,DISP=(OLD,DELETE)                          00000330
          ***                                                                     00000340          *** GENERATE COMMAND FILE TO DELETE TSO USER'S FILES AND ALIAS          00000350
          ***                                                                     00000360
  166     XXPW04     EXEC PGM=PSU002,COND=(0,NE,EVAL01),PARM=('\',                00000370
          XX             ' DELETE &ID..* NONVSAM SCRATCH PURGE\',                 00000380
          XX             ' DELETE &ID. ALIAS \',                                  00000390
          XX             ' SET LASTCC = 0\',                                      00000400
          XX             ' SET MAXCC = 0')                                        00000410

          ***                                                                     00000460
          *** DELETE TSO USER'S FILES AND ALIAS                                   00000470
          ***                                                                     00000480

  172     //ALLOC   EXEC PGM=IEFBR14
  173     //PWUP     DD  DISP=(,CATLG),DSN=SYS1.SECURE.PWUP,VOL=SER=MVS000,
          //             UNIT=3350,DCB=(RECFM=F,LRECL=18,BLKSIZE=18),
          //             SPACE=(TRK,(1,1))
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          *** Install auxiliary utilities needed by sample RACF-indication jobs *
          ***                                                                   *
          *** Expected return codes: Step RECEIVE: 00                           *
          ***                        Step INSTALL: 00                           *
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          ***
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          *** Receive distribution library                                      *
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          ***
  174     //RECEIVE  EXEC PGM=RECV370
  175     //STEPLIB  DD  DISP=SHR,DSN=SYSC.LINKLIB
  176     //XMITIN    DD DSN=SYSGEN.RAKF.V1R2M0.SAMPLIB(AUXUTILS),DISP=SHR
  177     //RECVLOG  DD  SYSOUT=*
  178     //SYSPRINT DD  SYSOUT=*

          //             DCB=(LRECL=0,BLKSIZE=19069,RECFM=U),UNIT=SYSDA
  182     //SYSIN     DD DUMMY
          ***
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          *** Copy utilities to system libraries                                *
          *** ------------------------------------------------------------------*
          ***
          *** Replace RAKFINIT
          ***
  183     //RKFINIT1 EXEC PGM=IEBGENER
  184     //SYSIN    DD *
  185     //SYSPRINT DD SYSOUT=*
  186     //SYSUT2   DD DSN=&&RAKFIN,
          //             UNIT=SYSDA,
          //             SPACE=(CYL,(1,1,1)),
          //             DISP=(,PASS)
  187     //SYSUT1   DD *
  188     //INSTALL  EXEC PGM=IEBCOPY
  189     //AUX      DD  DISP=(OLD,DELETE),DSN=&&AUX
  190     //LINKLIB  DD  DISP=SHR,DSN=SYS2.LINKLIB  191     //CMDLIB   DD  DISP=SHR,DSN=SYS2.CMDLIB
  192     //LPALIB   DD  DISP=SHR,DSN=SYS1.LPALIB
  193     //PARMLIB  DD  DISP=SHR,DSN=SYS1.PARMLIB
  194     //RAKFINIT DD  DISP=(OLD,PASS),DSN=&&RAKFIN
  195     //SYSPRINT DD  SYSOUT=*
  196     //SYSIN    DD  *
          *** ----------------------------------------------------------------- *
          *** This step adds the IBMUSER TSO USER ID and allocates default      *
          *** datasets for that user.                                           *
          *** ----------------------------------------------------------------- *
  197     //IBMUSER EXEC TSONUSER,ID=IBMUSER,   This will be the logon ID
          //        PW='SYS1',
          //        OP='OPER',             Allow operator authority
          //        AC='ACCT'              Allow ACCOUNT TSO COMMAND
          ***
          *** Add RAKF User and Profiles
          *** -----------------------------------------------------------------
          ***                                                                     00000010
          *** PROCEDURE TO ADD NEW TSO USER ID TO SYS1.UADS AND CREATE STANDARD   00000020
          *** SET OF USER FILES FOR THE NEW USER ID                               00000030
          ***                                                                     00000040
  198     XXTSONUSER PROC ID=,              TSO USER ID                          +00000050
          XX             PW='*',            TSO USER PASSWORD                    +00000060
          XX             AN='*',            ACCOUNT NUMBER                       +00000070
          XX             PR='IKJACCNT',     LOGON PROCEDURE                      +00000080
          XX             MS='NOLIM',        REGION LIMIT: MAXSIZE(N)/NOLIM       +00000090
          XX             OP='NOOPER',       OPERATOR CMNDS: OPER/NOOPER          +00000100
          XX             AC='NOACCT',       ACCOUNT CMD: ACCT/NOACCT             +00000110
          XX             JC='JCL',          JOB CONTROL: JCL/NOJCL               +00000120
          XX             MT='NOMOUNT',      TAPE MOUNT: MOUNT/NOMOUNT            +00000130
          XX             SZ='SIZE(4096)',   DEFAULT REGION SIZE                  +00000140
          XX             UN='UNIT(SYSDA)'   DYNAMIC ALLOCATION UNIT               00000150
          ***                                                                     00000160
          *** IF ANY FILES WE WILL CREATE FOR NEW USER'S ID EXIST, DELETE THEM    00000170
          ***                                                                     00000180
  199     XXDEL01    EXEC PGM=IEFBR14                                             00000190
  200     XXCLIST    DD  DSN=&ID..CLIST,DISP=(MOD,DELETE,DELETE),                 00000200
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,VOL=SER=PUB000,                               00000210
          XX             SPACE=(CYL,0),DCB=SYS1.CMDPROC                           00000220
  201     XXCNTL     DD  DSN=&ID..CNTL,DISP=(MOD,DELETE,DELETE),                  00000230
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,VOL=SER=PUB000,                               00000240
          XX             SPACE=(CYL,0),DCB=SYS1.MACLIB                            00000250
  202     XXSOURCE   DD  DSN=&ID..SOURCE,DISP=(MOD,DELETE,DELETE),                00000260
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,VOL=SER=PUB000,                               00000270
          XX             SPACE=(CYL,0),DCB=SYS1.MACLIB                            00000280
  203     XXLOAD     DD  DSN=&ID..LOAD,DISP=(MOD,DELETE,DELETE),                  00000290
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,VOL=SER=PUB000,                               00000300
          XX             SPACE=(CYL,0),DCB=SYS1.LINKLIB                           00000310
          ***                                                                     00000320
          *** ALLOCATE STANDARD FILES FOR NEW USER'S ID                           00000330
          ***                                                                     00000340
  204     XXAL02     EXEC PGM=IEFBR14                                             00000350
  205     XXCLIST    DD  DSN=&ID..CLIST,DISP=(,KEEP,DELETE),                      00000360
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,VOL=SER=PUB000,                               00000370
          XX             SPACE=(CYL,(1,1,20)),DCB=SYS1.CMDPROC                    00000380
  206     XXCNTL     DD  DSN=&ID..CNTL,DISP=(,KEEP,DELETE),                       00000390
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,VOL=SER=PUB000,                               00000400
          XX             SPACE=(CYL,(1,1,20)),DCB=SYS1.MACLIB                     00000410
  207     XXSOURCE   DD  DSN=&ID..SOURCE,DISP=(,KEEP,DELETE),                     00000420
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,VOL=SER=PUB000,                               00000430
          XX             SPACE=(CYL,(1,1,20)),DCB=SYS1.MACLIB                     00000440  208     XXLOAD     DD  DSN=&ID..LOAD,DISP=(,KEEP,DELETE),                       00000450
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,VOL=SER=PUB000,                               00000460
          XX             SPACE=(CYL,(1,1,20)),DCB=SYS1.LINKLIB                    00000470
          ***                                                                     00000480
          *** GENERATE COMMAND FILE TO CREATE NEW USER'S PROFILE                  00000490
          ***                                                                     00000500
  209     XXPW03     EXEC PGM=PSU002,PARM=('\',                                   00000510
          XX             ' PROFILE NOPREFIX\',                                    00000520
          XX             ' ACCOUNT\',                                             00000530
          XX             '   SYNC')                                               00000540
  210     XXSTEPLIB  DD  DSN=SYSC.LINKLIB,DISP=SHR                                00000550
  211     XXSYSOUT   DD  DSN=&&ACCOUNT,DISP=(,PASS),                              00000560
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,SPACE=(TRK,(15)),                             00000570
          XX             DCB=(RECFM=FB,LRECL=80,BLKSIZE=3120)                     00000580
  212     XXPW04     EXEC PGM=PSU002,PARM=('\',                                   00000590
          XX             '   DELETE (&ID.)\',                                     00000600
          XX             '   ADD (&ID. &PW. &AN. &PR.) +\',                       00000610
          XX             '       &MS. +')                                         00000620
  213     XXSTEPLIB  DD  DSN=SYSC.LINKLIB,DISP=SHR                                00000630
  214     XXSYSOUT   DD  DSN=&&ACCOUNT,DISP=(MOD,PASS)                            00000640
  215     XXPW05     EXEC PGM=PSU002,PARM=('\',                                   00000650
          XX             '       &OP. +\',                                        00000660

          XX             '       &SZ. +\',                                        00000730

  220     XXSYSOUT   DD  DSN=&&ACCOUNT,DISP=(MOD,PASS)                            00000790
          ***                                                                     00000800
          *** CREATE NEW USER'S PROFILE                                           00000810

  222     XXSYSUADS   DD DSN=SYS1.UADS,DISP=SHR                                   00000840

  225     XXSYSTSIN   DD DSN=&&ACCOUNT,DISP=(OLD,DELETE)                          00000870
          ***                                                                     00000880
          *** GENERATE COMMAND FILE TO 1) DEFINE ALIAS FOR NEW USER'S ID          00000890
          *** AND 2) DEFINE CATALOG ENTRIES FOR FILES FOR NEW USER                00000900
          ***                                                                     00000910
  226     XXPW08     EXEC PGM=PSU002,PARM=('\',                                   00000920
          XX             ' DELETE &ID..* NOSCRATCH \',                            00000930
          XX             ' DELETE &ID. ALIAS \',                                  00000940
          XX             ' SET LASTCC = 0')                                       00000950
  227     XXSTEPLIB  DD  DSN=SYSC.LINKLIB,DISP=SHR                                00000960
  228     XXSYSOUT   DD  DSN=&&IDCAMS,DISP=(,PASS),                               00000970
          XX             UNIT=SYSDA,SPACE=(TRK,(15)),                             00000980
          XX             DCB=(RECFM=FB,LRECL=80,BLKSIZE=3120)                     00000990

                                      6 *  Type: Assembler source                                             *
                                      7 *                                                                     *
                                      8 *  Desc: Type 3/4 SVC for setting/unsetting JSCBAUTH                  *
                                      9 *                                                                     *
                                     10 *        If a security system (for example RAKF) is installed         *
                                     11 *        read access to ressource SVC244 in class FACILITY is         *
                                     12 *        requested and the JSCBAUTH change is made only if the        *
                                     13 *        security system grants this access                           *

                                     15 *  Regs at Entry:                                                     *
                                     16 *                                                                     *
                                     17 *          R0 must be 0                                               *
                                     18 *          R1 = Request code.  R1 = 1 ===> Authon                     *

                                     20 *          R2       undetermined                                      *
                                     21 *          R3  ---> CVT                                               *
                                     22 *          R4  ---> TCB                                               *
                                     23 *          R5  ---> SVRB                                              *
                                     24 *          R6  ---> Entry point                                       *
                                     25 *          R7  ---> ASCB                                              *
                                     26 *          R8  ---> undetermined                                      *
